# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok ivory coast 's three rebel groups will not attend a meeting of west african leaders in the capital city yamoussoukro on monday to discuss the country 's five-month war , rebel leader guillaume soro said here sunday .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Guillaume"
                  :op2 "Soro")
            :ARG0-of (l / lead-02
                  :ARG1 (r / rebel-01)))
      :ARG1 (a / attend-01
            :polarity -
            :ARG0 (g / group
                  :quant 3
                  :ARG0-of (r2 / rebel-01)
                  :location (c / coast
                        :mod (c2 / country
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Ivory"
                                    :op2 "Coast"))))
            :ARG1 (m / meet-03
                  :ARG0 (p2 / person
                        :ARG0-of (l2 / lead-02
                              :ARG1 (w / world-region
                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "West"
                                          :op2 "Africa"))))
                  :location (c3 / city
                        :name (n4 / name
                              :op1 "Yamoussoukro")
                        :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                              :ARG1 (c4 / country)
                              :ARG2 (c5 / capital)))
                  :time (d / date-entity
                        :weekday (m2 / monday))
                  :purpose (d2 / discuss-01
                        :ARG0 p2
                        :ARG1 (w2 / war-01
                              :ARG0 c4
                              :duration (t / temporal-quantity
                                    :quant 5
                                    :unit (m3 / month)))
                        :ARG2 g)))
      :location (h2 / here)
      :time d
      :weekday (s2 / sunday))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok following are some of the major international news stories scheduled to be covered or pursued by xinhua on monday .
# ::alignments
(f / follow-01
      :ARG2 (s / story
            :quant (s2 / some)
            :ARG1-of (ii / include-91
                  :ARG2 (s3 / story
                        :mod (n / news)
                        :mod (ii2 / international)
                        :ARG1-of (m / major-02)
                        :ARG1-of (c / cover-03
                              :ARG0 (p / publication
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Xinhua"))
                              :time (d / date-entity
                                    :weekday (m2 / monday)))
                        :ARG1-of (p2 / pursue-01
                              :ARG0 p)))))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

      :ARG0 (p / person

                  :op2 "Sharon")

                  :ARG1 (c / country
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Israel"))
                  :ARG2 (m / minister
                        :mod (p2 / prime))))
      :ARG1 (c2 / call-03
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (c3 / coordinate-01
                  :ARG1 (s / side
                        :quant 2)
                  :time (w / withdraw-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 c
                        :ARG2 (s2 / strip
                              :mod (c4 / city
                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "Gaza")))
                        :ARG1-of (p3 / plan-01
                              :ARG0 c)
                        :time (d / date-entity
                              :season (s3 / summer)
                              :mod (y / year
                                    :mod (t / this))))))
      :time (d2 / due-03
            :ARG1 (p4 / person
                  :name (n4 / name
                        :op1 "Mahmoud"
                        :op2 "Abbas")
                  :ARG0-of (l / lead-02
                        :ARG1 (c5 / country
                              :name (n5 / name
                                    :op1 "Palestine"))))
            :location (g / government-organization
                  :name (n6 / name
                        :op1 "White"
                        :op2 "House"))
            :time (w2 / week
                  :mod (t2 / this))))

# ::id 3 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok german chancellor gerhard schroder monday announced his government will provide ### million euro to promote cooperation on renewable energies over the next five years .
# ::alignments
(a / announce-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Gerhard"
                  :op2 "Schroder")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG2 (c / chancellor))
            :mod (c2 / country
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "Germany")))
      :ARG1 (p2 / provide-01
            :ARG0 (g / government-organization
                  :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01
                        :ARG1 p))
            :ARG1 (m / monetary-quantity
                  :quant 10000000
                  :unit (e / euro))
            :ARG2 (p3 / promote-02
                  :ARG0 g
                  :ARG1 (c3 / cooperate-01
                        :ARG2 (e2 / energy
                              :ARG1-of (r / renew-01
                                    :ARG1-of (p4 / possible-01))))
                  :time (a2 / after
                        :op1 (n3 / now)
                        :duration (t / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 5
                              :unit (y / year)))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (m2 / monday)))

                        :op1 "Croatia")))

            :ARG1 (r / row
                  :mod (b / border)
                  :ARG1-of (r2 / run-13
                        :ARG1-of (l / long-03)))
            :ARG3 (o / organization
                  :name (n3 / name
                        :op1 "International"
                        :op2 "Court"
                        :op3 "of"
                        :op4 "Justice")))
      :ARG2 o
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (s / sunday)))

            :degree (f / further))
      :mod (a3 / again)
      :time (w / wednesday)

            :ARG1 (r / round
                  :ord (o3 / ordinal-entity
                        :value 1)

                        :ARG2 (t / talk-01

                              :time (j / just))))))

# ::id 14 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok a new report on millions of smallpox vaccinations given in the ####s confirms that there is a small but significant risk that newly vaccinated people can make others seriously ill by infecting them with <unk> , the virus used in the vaccine .
# ::alignments
(c / confirm-01
      :ARG0 (r / report-01
            :ARG1 (v / vaccinate-01
                  :ARG2 (d / disease
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Smallpox"))
                  :quant (m / multiple
                        :op1 1000000))
            :ARG1-of (n2 / new-01)
            :medium (p / publication
                  :name n
                  :op1 "The"
                  :op2 "###s"))
      :ARG1 (r2 / risk-01
            :ARG1 (p2 / possible-01
                  :ARG1 (m2 / make-02
                        :ARG0 (p3 / person
                              :ARG1-of (v2 / vaccinate-01
                                    :ARG1-of n2)))
                  :ARG1 (ii / ill-01
                        :ARG1 (p4 / person
                              :mod (o / other))
                        :ARG1-of (s / serious-02))
                  :ARG2 (ii2 / infect-01
                        :ARG0 p3
                        :ARG1 p4
                        :ARG2 (v3 / virus
                              :name n
                              :op1 "innocuous")
                        :ARG1-of (u / use-01
                              :ARG2 v))))
      :mod (s2 / small)
      :ARG1-of (s3 / significant-02
            :polarity -))
